5:
There are so many different kinds of
yokai out there, huh? Not just scary
ones either.
7:
You were really amazing too, Kugui. I
had no idea you could fight like that.
14: Yeah, a bit. I'm from the East, after all.
16:
But when I'm painting, I forget about
stuff like that. I just love art too much.
21:
...What made you start painting in
the first place?
25:
Hmm, it just kinda happened, I
guess?
28:
About 3 months back, I got really
annoyed that the next chapter of
KoiAzu wasn't out yet, so I went
knocking on Master's door.
34:
Please! I'll do the dishes, clean the
house... Whatever chores you need
done!
36:
Just keep making more KoiAzu!
That's all I want!
40:
You're one annoying brat, y'know!
None of that's gonna help me with
inspiration!
44:
Then I'll grab whatever materials
and references you need! Just
please keep painting!
48:
Yeah? If you're that desperate, then
I've got another idea.
51:
Become my disciple, and paint the
stuff I need to be inspired. Every. Day.
53: Then you'll have your next chapter!
59:
You became his disciple... Just like
that?
62:
When you put it that way... Guess he
and I are both kinda crazy, huh?
65:
But I don't regret my decision—not
one bit.
68:
I didn't have anything to pour my
heart into before I started painting.
It's seriously changed my life!
72:
Hold on... You only started painting
when you became his disciple... 3
months ago?
79:
Your art is incredible for such a short
span of time...
83:
Ahaha, only because I had a good
teacher. Master's kind of a pain in
the butt, but he's also a genius when
it comes to art and story writing.
86:
When it comes to style though, I'm
aiming for something different than
his... and more like...
92:
Did I hear someone mention KoiAzu?
It is always wonderful to meet a
fellow fan! May I join in?
96:
Of course!
Wow, I never thought I'd have the
chance to talk with the real Princess
Inaho...
111:
Wow... Even without your power, your
art looks like it's about to pop right
out of the page.
115:
I'm simply depicting what I see.
Ryouki is far more skilled than me.
118:
You think so? If you ask me, you're
both real good at what you do...
122:
She began painting only 3 months
ago.
128:
Not only is she more talented, but...
She also enjoys what she does and
pursues it without hesitation.
130:
We are not on the same level
whatsoever.
134:
I guess I can understand where
you're coming from.
137:
Watching someone be amazing
and charge ahead, all while you're
standing there lost...
139:
You can't be exactly like them—but
you can look up to them.
144: Yes! Ryouki is truly amazing, and I...
148:
I don't want to lose to her. The
sentiment is silly, I know, but...
152:
Heh, you've got nothing to worry
about. You'll give Ryouki a run for her
money for sure.
159: So am I. Keep your chin up!
161:
Show Gramp Zigza and Ryouki what
you're really made of!
165:
Kugui, this subject has eyes. Does
this mean you are finished?
173:
...It's not leaping out on its own? But
why?
179:
Perhaps you should try animating it
on purpose.
181:
This could be an opportunity to
better grasp your power. I don't
sense anything amiss with the
painting as is.
184:
That's true, but it's still possible it
could run amok...
189:
The yokai you drew isn't a
particularly strong one. We could
take it down if that happened.
191:
Besides, you have a waiting
audience.
197:
I want to see this work of art in
motion. Very, very much.
206: ...All right, then I... I'll do it.
227:
I've never seen a yokai so relaxed!
It's almost kinda cute!
245:
Looks like we gotta do it the hard
way! You ready, Kugui?
